### list everything about a pool (volume,snapshot)

zfs list -t all [pool_name]

bootfs is a property of the pool, which points to the dataset used for booting - 
Ie: bootfs={POOLNAME}/{ROOT DATASET}/boot

-O = filesystem prop
-o  = pool prop
zpool create -O <fsprop>=<val> poolname
zpool create -o <poolprop>=<val> poolname

zpool initialize -auc (all,cancel,uninitialize) all pools
zpool initialize poolname


Zpool scrub -Cea
